Classdroid is a student/teacher android app used to take pictures and instantly upload them to a learning portfolio/blog or other publishing platform.

Classdroid is designed to work in the classroom / education for assessment and recording pupil achievement.

Classdroid currently only supports Wordpress however Moodle and other platform support can be added with some minor code modifications.

Classdroid currently only supports android devices.   iPhone support will require a port.

Classdroid is availalbe in the Google Market Place as a free download.

We recommend blogs from PrimaryBlogger.